a chance to blow up a second time.

566
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:53,000
This one gives a chance for projectiles

567
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:55,000
to rebound off terrain,

568
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:57,000
as well as giving you some pierce chance

569
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,000
to make that more likely.

570
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,000
Note that even though this is

571
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,000
in the mercenary section,

572
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,000
this would work with projectiles

573
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:04,000
from all classes,

574
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,000
so there are often reasons

575
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,000
to go to different areas of the tree.

576
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:10,000
In order to get between these clusters,

577
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,000
you will generally have to allocate nodes

578
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,000
in the attribute highways.

579
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,000
Attribute nodes allow you to pick

580
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,000
which attribute you would like to use,

581
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,000
so it's very easy to get points

582
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,000
for any attribute that your gear might need.

583
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,000
You can change which attribute

584
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,000
these nodes give you for half price

585
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,000
at the respec vendor.

586
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,000
In addition to notables,

587
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,000
you will also find even larger passives

588
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,000
called keystones.

589
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,000
Keystones have both an upside

590
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,000
and a downside,

591
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,000
and often require changing your entire build

592
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,000
to design around them.

593
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:39,000
A great example is Giant's Blood,

594
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,000
which allows you to wield two-hand weapons

595
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:42,000
in a single hand,

596
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:44,000
but doubles the attribute requirements off them.

597
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,000
You can use a two-hand mace with a shield,

598
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,000
or even dual-wield them.

599
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,000
Or how about Mind Over Matter,

600
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,000
which makes all damage go to your mana pool first

601
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,000
before your life pool,

602
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,000
but you lose 50% of your mana regen.

603
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,000
Skills like these can be tough to build around,

604
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,000
but if you're up for the challenge,

605
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,000
they can be very rewarding.

606
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:02,000
As we showed you earlier on the Sorceress,

607
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,000
you can swap between weapon sets on the fly

608
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,000
as you use certain skills.

609
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,000
One of the new features in Path of Exile 2's passive tree

610
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,000
is that you can choose to have your passive tree

611
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:10,000
to have your passive tree

612
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,000
and use your mana pool.

613
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,000
You can swap between weapon sets on the fly

614
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,000
as you use certain skills.

615
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,000
One of the new features in Path of Exile 2's passive tree

616
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,000
is that you can choose to have your passive tree

617
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,000
change as you switch between weapon sets

618
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:20,000
to take advantage of specific bonuses on the tree.

619
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,000
For the Sorceress,

620
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,000
you might want to change between

621
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:25,000
fire and lightning specialization.

622
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,000
Or you could switch between one-hand

623
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:27,000
and a two-hand setup

624
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,000
in order to be able to block boss attacks

625
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:30,000
while following up with heavy hits

626
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,000
from your bigger mace.

627
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:33,000
Or perhaps you could have a full curse setup

628
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,000
on your witch to debuff enemies

629
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,000
before switching to a chaos degen build

630
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,000
for maximum damage.

631
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,000
If you're able to block boss attacks

632
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,000
or you could have a full curse setup

633
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,000
on your witch to debuff enemies

634
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,000
before switching to a chaos degen build

635
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,000
for maximum damage.

636
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,000
If you want to stick with just one weapon set,

637
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,000
you can just use these specialization points

638
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,000
as bonus points to invest however you like.

639
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,000
But creative players will find plenty of opportunities

640
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,000
with this system.

641
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:59,000
You can get weapon specialization points

642
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:00,000
throughout the campaign

643
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,000
from optional bosses and quests.

644
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,000
For example,

645
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,000
if I manage to defeat the Crowbell,

646
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:07,000
I'll get a weapon specialization book.

647
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,000
There are lots of other permanent boosts

648
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,000
available from the campaign too.

649
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,000
On the map you can see icons that indicate

650
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:15,000
the many optional encounters you can find.

651
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,000
Some of them have permanent character boosts

652
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,000
and others have powerful items.

653
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:21,000
If you're having trouble getting past a boss,

654
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:23,000
it might be a good idea to explore

655
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,000
and see what you can find.

656
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,000
For example,

657
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,000
if you defeat Blackjaw the Remnant,

658
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:29,000
you'll gain a permanent increase to fire resistance.

659
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:32,000
One of the most important finds are spirit bonuses.

660
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:36,000
You can find the first one here in the canopy in Act 1.

661
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Defeat the boss in this area

662
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,000
to acquire a permanent addition of spirit.

663
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,000
The permanent buffs you gain from spirit are very powerful,

664
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,000
and every class will find the use for them,

665
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:47,000
so make sure you hunt down these upgrades.

666
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:49,000
There's one in each act.

667
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,000
Now we haven't even talked about

668
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,000
the most important element of character progression, items.

669
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:55,000
That's why we're all here, right?

670
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:57,000
Items in Path of Exile can be broken down

671
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,000
into four rarity groups,

672
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Normal, Magic, Rare and Unique.

673
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,000
One of the things you're going to want to do

674
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,000
as you play through the campaign

675
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,000
is upgrade the items you find,

676
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,000
and you can do that with currency items.

677
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,000
An Orb of Transmutation will allow you

678
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
to upgrade a normal item to a magic item with one mod.

679
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,000
You can then apply an Orb of Augmentation

680
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,000
to add a second mod,

681
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,000
then use a Regal Orb to add a third mod,

682
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,000
and upgrade it to a rare.

683
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,000
Finally, you can use some Exalted Orbs

684
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:28,000
to add more mods to your rare to a total of six mods.

685
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:31,000
One of the things we think is really important

686
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:34,000
is to make these options available to use as you play.

687
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,000
All the items that add mods are much more common

688
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,000
than they were in Path of Exile 1,

689
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,000
so that you can use them throughout your campaign playthrough.

690
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,000
We want you to find things on the ground

691
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:45,000
that can be crafted into upgrades much more frequently.

692
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
As well as making the drop rates on these items

693
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,000
much more common,

694
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
you can also get them by disenchanting unwanted gear

695
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,000
at the magic item vendor.

696
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,000
If you disenchant magic items,

697
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:58,000
you can build up to an Orb of Transmutation,

698
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,000
and by disenchanting rares,

699
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,000
you can build up to Regal Orbs.

700
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:05,000
Another important area of crafting items in PoE2 is sockets.

701
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,000
Some items you find will have sockets

702
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,000
that can have Ezimite runes placed in them

703
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,000
that add more mods to the item.

704
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,000
If I insert this glacial rune into my helmet,

705
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,000
it will give extra cold resistance.

706
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,000
This is a great way to solve problems

707
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,000
that you have with your build,

708
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,000
like resistances or damage.

709
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:23,000
If you find socketed items that you don't have a use for,

710
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,000
you can take them to the salvage bench in town

711
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:27,000
to work towards an artificer's orb.

712
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:30,000
This will allow you to add sockets to your existing items.

713
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:33,000
Body armours and two-hand weapons can have up to two sockets,

714
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,000
while the rest of your armour and one-hand weapons

715
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
can only have one socket.

716
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,000
You can also salvage items with quality

717
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,000
to create items like armour scraps or whetstones.

718
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,000
These will allow you to increase the quality of your items

719
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:46,000
for an up to 20% boost.

720
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
If you don't want to disenchant or salvage your items,

721
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,000
you can always sell them for gold.

722
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,000
Gold can be used to buy items from vendors,

723
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,000
and we've tried to do a lot to make sure

724
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,000
that the items they have for sale are actually useful.

725
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:59,000
Every time you level up, they get more stock,

726
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:01,000
so make sure to check back often.

727
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:04,000
Other vendors offer a gamble.

728
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,000
Pay a flat amount of gold,

729
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,000
and you'll get a random item of a specific type.

730
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:10,000
This could be a great way to improve your gear,

731
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,000
if you're lucky.

732
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:14,000
Gold is also used to respec your passive skills.

733
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Take advantage of this system to experiment with your tree

734
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
and rework it as required.

735
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:21,000
The other thing you might want to use gold for

736
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,000
is the currency exchange.

737
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:24,000
This allows you to exchange currency items

738
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,000
with other players on an open market,

739
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,000
in exchange for a small gold fee.

740
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:31,000
Now, all items in Path of Exile are freely tradable.

741
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:34,000
We never bind anything to your character, except gold.

742
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,000
Now, most gear in Path of Exile 2 is randomly generated,

743
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:43,000
but there's another type that isn't.

744
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Uniques.

745
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,000
They are especially rare,

746
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,000
each with a handcrafted set of unusual mods

747
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,000
which can dramatically change a character's build.

748
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,000
They're not just better rare items.

749
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,000
They can do much stranger things

750
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:56,000
that can fundamentally change your character.

751
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Corpse Wade will make any corpses you run through

752
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,000
explode into clouds of poison.

753
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:06,000
The Sands of Silk is a body armour that changes your dodge roll

754
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:10,000
into a blink, morphing you into sand as you teleport past your foes.

755
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:13,000
And of course, some uniques are just pure hits of dopamine,

756
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
like Quill Rain, which just turns your bow attacks into full auto

757
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,000
by doubling your attack speed.

758
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Each unique is something that you can build your character around.

759
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:25,000
We try to make sure that most unique items have a potential use at endgame,

760
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,000
even if you find them early on.

761
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:32,000
And as you can see, every single unique item comes with custom art to match.

762
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:38,000
The last character progression system that you can do during the campaign is Ascension.

763
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
Starting in Act 2, you will come across Ascension Trials,

764
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,000
tests that you must complete to unlock your Ascension class.

765
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:46,000
We'll explain these trials soon,

766
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:49,000
but first let's take a look at what Ascending can do for your character.

767
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,000
Each class has access to three Ascendancy classes,

768
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,000
but at the start of early access, only two per class will be available.

769
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,000
Ascendancy classes are unique to each character class,

770
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,000
so choose wisely.

771
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,000
They can drastically affect how you build your character.

772
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,000
As a Sorceress, you could become a Stormweaver,

773
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,000
a master of the elements.

774
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:11,000
Tempest Caller causes elemental storms to be summoned

775
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:13,000
each time you do a critical hit with a spell.

776
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,000
With Strike Twice, you can stack two copies of Shock for more damage,

777
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
and going deeper into the tree,

778
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
you can make all your damage-type supply Shock.

779
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Make a Shock build from any skill.

780
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:29,000
Alternatively, you could become a Chronomancer and command time itself.

781
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:33,000
She literally has the ability to stop time with Time Freeze.

782
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:36,000
Not only that, but she has many other time manipulation abilities.

783
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Using Temporal Rift, she can teleport back to a previous location,

784
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:43,000
resetting her life and mana back to what it was.

785
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,000
Or with Time Snap, she can reset all her cooldowns

786
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,000
and cast all her spells again.

787
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:52,000
On the Warrior, you can choose between the Warbringer or the Titan.

788
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,000
The Warbringer channels the might of his ancestors

789
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,000
to gain tremendous power.

790
00:35:57,000 --> 00:36:00,000
Using Answered Call, you can summon ancestral spirits

791
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,000
linked to each of your totems.

792
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:05,000
With Jade Heritage, you can encase your body in a protective layer

793
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:07,000
that absorbs all damage until it breaks.

794
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:12,000
Warcaller's Bellow allows you to explode the corpses of your enemies.

795
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:16,000
And with Great Wolf's Howl, you can ignore the cooldowns of your Warcries.

796
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,000
Let all that anger out.

797
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,000
The Titan class is all about hitting big.

798
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:26,000
With Earthbreaker, every slam is a chance to create an Aftershock.

799
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,000
With Crushing Impacts, every hit becomes a Crushing Blow,

800
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:33,000
which will allow you to stun your enemies with ease.

801
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:37,000
With Surprising Strength, you can take advantage of stunned enemies

802
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,000
to deal 40% more damage.

803
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:43,000
As a Ranger, you might choose to be a Deadeye,

804
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:47,000
an expert markswoman who can take down foes with style.

805
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:51,000
With endless munitions, every attack gains an extra projectile.

806
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:56,000
With Gathering Winds, she gains a small increase to movement speed

807
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,000
with every attack.

808
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:59,000
But be careful, she loses them when getting hit.

809
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:05,000
With Eagle Eyes, she will never miss, allowing you to stop wasting all those passer points on accuracy.

810
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:11,000
Alternatively, you could become a Pathfinder, the master of flasks and poison.

811
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:14,000
She can choose from one of several throwable concoctions,

812
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:17,000
allowing her to spend her flask charges to throw explosive bottles

813
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:19,000
that deal various types of damage.

814
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:22,000
A Bleeding Concoction will make your enemies bleed,

815
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:26,000
while a fulminating one can shock your enemies, allowing you to do extra damage.

816
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:29,000
Contagious Contamination allows her to spread poisons between her foes,

817
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:35,000
while Overwhelming Toxicity doubles the number of stacks they can be infected by.

818
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:40,000
Running Assault allows her to move much more quickly while firing,

819
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:44,000
while Relentless Pursuit makes her totally immune to being slowed by enemies.

820
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:49,000
The Witch can ascend into the Infernalist or the Blood Mage.

821
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:53,000
As an Infernalist, she can summon a loyal Hellhound companion.

822
