978
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:13,000
Hi, I'm Mark Roberts, Game Director on Path of Exile 2.

979
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:20,000
Well, one thing that Path of Exile is known for is having a lot of distinct Endgame content to choose between.

980
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:30,000
Each Endgame mechanic needs to have its own progression system, areas, bosses, rewards, and player power that can only be gained from that content.

981
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:37,000
We are going to be adding a lot more over time, but for Path of Exile 2 we decided to start with seven distinct systems you can progress through.

982
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:43,000
This is the Atlas, and it serves as the core of the Endgame for Path of Exile 2.

983
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:46,000
It's infinite and expands in all directions.

984
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:53,000
Now, we are not going to spoil the plot too much here, but corruption from the beast has blighted the land, and your objective is to help fight it.

985
00:50:53,000 --> 00:51:01,000
In the center of the Atlas you will find the Ziggurat, a temple in which the Vaal research the fundamentals of space and time.

986
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:07,000
Here, we can open portals to nearby locations and begin cleansing corruption and finding resources.

987
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:11,000
In order to power the portal device, we will need Waystones.

988
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:16,000
Each waystone has a tier which will determine the level of the monsters that you will face.

989
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:21,000
To go to an area, simply click one that is adjacent to an area that you have already completed.

990
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:24,000
Insert the waystone and click Traverse.

991
00:51:24,000 --> 00:51:28,000
Portals will open, allowing you and your party to travel to the area you have selected.

992
00:51:28,000 --> 00:51:35,000
All the areas in the Endgame feel distinct from the locations in the campaign, and we have dialed the randomization up to 11.

993
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:42,000
The monster packs you will face in each map are totally random, and the combination of them can lead to some very interesting combat situations.

994
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:48,000
There are over 400 monster types in early access, and they have a lot of varied and interesting abilities.

995
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:53,000
Depending on which combinations you face, you might find some serious challenges.

996
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:59,000
In order to cleanse the corruption from the area, you will need to defeat all the powerful rare and unique enemies in it.

997
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:02,000
Once you have done that, the area will be marked as completed,

998
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:06,000
and you will be able to travel past it to progress deeper into the world.

999
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:12,000
If you die, then the map can no longer be run, and you will have to find another way around to get to the areas behind it.

1000
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:17,000
There are also all kinds of other random encounters you might run into as you play maps.

1001
00:52:17,000 --> 00:52:20,000
One such encounter are Precursor Artifacts.

1002
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:24,000
These are ancient, corrupting monuments that irradiate the monsters around them.

1003
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:27,000
The monsters that feed off the corruption are drawn to their power.

1004
00:52:27,000 --> 00:52:31,000
If you defeat the monsters and cleanse the artifact, you will get a powerful temporary buff.

1005
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:39,000
Some of the buffs make you faster, others rain lightning or fire around you, and some even give you increased experience or help you find better items.

1006
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:42,000
You can also find Strong Boxes.

1007
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:46,000
These enigmatic chests guard piles of treasure, but are always a trap.

1008
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:54,000
Monsters lie in wait to attack you the moment you open it, and the boxes often have mechanisms to unleash powerful spells or dangerous debuffs.

1009
00:52:54,000 --> 00:53:02,000
There are different types of Strong Boxes containing different items, and you can even use your currency items to craft them on the fly, so you can optimize the content.

1010
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:14,000
But be careful of opening one you can't handle.

1011
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:17,000
Sometimes you'll discover monsters frozen in essences.

1012
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,000
Solidified, crystalline corruption.

1013
00:53:19,000 --> 00:53:21,000
These dangerous monsters can be broken free.

1014
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:28,000
If you defeat them, the essence they drop can be used to upgrade normal items to magic items with a guaranteed mod from a category.

1015
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:34,000
For example, we could use this one on some boots to ensure a movement speed mod.

1016
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:43,000
Rarely, essences will also drop that allow you to upgrade magics to rares, adding the guaranteed mod.

1017
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:59,000
This is incredibly powerful since it allows you to get a second deterministic mod in your crafting projects.

1018
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:06,000
Combining these with the currencies that are commonly found in Rayclass for modifying items, and we can get a very nice pair of boots indeed.

1019
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:13,000
Waystones, like all items, can also be crafted using your currency items.

1020
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:19,000
Adding prefix mods will improve the rewards, while suffix mods increase danger.

1021
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:24,000
The more dangerous a map is, the more waystones will drop.

1022
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:31,000
Adding mods to your waystones is key to progressing to higher tiers and sustaining them, but it will require you to take on larger challenges.

1023
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:37,000
There are a variety of factors you have to consider when crafting your waystones.

1024
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:45,000
Some maps will have higher density, some lower, some have more magic and rare chests, or monsters, some are more linear, and others more open.

1025
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:50,000
Make sure you explore and think about what makes certain maps good if you want to maximise your returns.

1026
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:58,000
As you cleanse corruption from higher and higher tiers of the Atlas, you will gain points that you can spend in the Atlas tree.

1027
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:03,000
This tree allows you to juice the danger and rewards of all areas in the endgame.

1028
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:11,000
You could increase the number of monsters, the number of rares, the number of precursor artifacts or strongboxes, even the quantity of item drops.

1029
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:19,000
As you explore the endgame world map, you'll notice various different biomes, from snow-capped mountains to dense jungle valleys.

1030
00:55:19,000 --> 00:55:22,000
Most maps are restricted to certain biomes.

1031
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:27,000
As you continue to explore deeper into the Atlas, there are all sorts of things to discover.

1032
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:32,000
These cities are constructed by different peoples of Rhaeclast, and have specific items that can be found there.

1033
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:36,000
These strange structures marked on the map don't appear to do anything for now.

1034
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:39,000
Perhaps you'll work out how to use them later.

1035
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:47,000
You might find unique maps like Untainted Paradise, an undisturbed island full of beasts that give an extreme amount of experience.

1036
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:52,000
You may even find a lonely man just enjoying his retirement who will give you a unique item for free.

1037
00:55:52,000 --> 00:55:57,000
In addition, you can find special areas that would make a good spot to set up camp.

1038
00:55:57,000 --> 00:56:02,000
Clear these areas of their hostile inhabitants, and you'll be able to claim them as your own hideout.

1039
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:09,000
You can decorate your hideout as you see fit, and invite various NPCs to join you there to create your own personal base of options.

1040
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:11,000
Explorations.

1041
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:15,000
A great tool for exploration are towers.

1042
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:18,000
These mysterious precursor constructs are dotted around the Atlas.

1043
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:24,000
Completing the tower will reveal a large area around it, allowing you to scout out your next challenge.

1044
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:27,000
There are lots of things to find, so keep looking.

1045
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:31,000
Some sections of your Atlas are influenced by corruption.

1046
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:36,000
This adds extra modifiers to the maps in the region, increasing difficulty and rewards.

1047
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:45,000
Here, slaying monsters in close proximity to each other will cause the vestiges of corruption within them to merge together, forming powerful and grotesque abominations.

1048
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:50,000
You may have noticed while looking at the Atlas that some of the areas have these icons above them.

1049
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:54,000
The icon indicates that the area contains some kind of special encounter.

1050
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:58,000
This icon indicates that the area has a powerful boss.

1051
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:04,000
Because only one in four maps contain a map boss, we are able to make them very powerful and very rewarding.

1052
00:57:04,000 --> 00:57:11,000
These bosses come from the campaign, but have had their difficulty increased with changes to AI and some of their abilities.

1053
00:57:11,000 --> 00:57:16,000
It's worth noting that because you can see where the bosses are, you can choose to take them on or avoid them.

1054
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:23,000
If you do choose to hunt bosses though, then you will be rewarded with special points for the boss hunting section of the Atlas skill tree.

1055
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:29,000
The points here will allow you to specialise in boss killing, giving you much greater rewards for defeating them.

1056
00:57:31,000 --> 00:57:40,000
For each different type of content in the endgame, we are adding specialised trees in order to make it so you don't feel the need to respec your points when you change between different types of content.

1057
00:57:40,000 --> 00:57:45,000
We will be showing you seven of these by the end of this presentation, so there is still a lot more to come.

1058
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:52,000
Bosses are not the only icon you will see on the Atlas. Let's take a look at one of the endgame systems, Breach.

1059
00:57:52,000 --> 00:57:59,000
If you played PoE 1, you might be familiar with Breach. For PoE 2, we have created sequels to several PoE 1 leagues.

1060
00:57:59,000 --> 00:58:05,000
While the mechanic is familiar, the monsters, bosses, rewards and progression are all new.

1061
00:58:05,000 --> 00:58:14,000
A Breach is a tear in the fabric of reality. Opening it will allow you to see the demons and otherworldly monstrosities that lie in wait on this other plane of existence.

1062
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:19,000
By engaging with a Breach, you'll create a bridge between their world and Rayquast.

1063
00:58:19,000 --> 00:58:23,000
In order to keep the Breach open, you will need to kill the demons that pour forth.

1064
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:28,000
The faster you can kill the monsters, the more monsters you will fight and the more loot you will find.

1065
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:33,000
You can also find clasped hands that will open and drop more items if you run over them.

1066
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:38,000
These can be a good boost to the rewards of the Breach, so keep an eye on them.

1067
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:44,000
One of the rewards that you may find while fighting monsters from Breach are Tablets.

1068
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:50,000
Tablets are special items that can be used with Precursor Towers to add more encounters to the Atlas.

1069
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:58,000
Breaches will drop Breach Tablets. Clicking on a completed tower will allow you to consume the tablet to add more breaches to areas within range of the tower.

1070
00:58:58,000 --> 00:59:07,000
This makes all the content in the Atlas self-sustaining. Want to do more Breaches? Find the tablets, add them to your towers, get more Breaches, getting more tablets.

1071
00:59:07,000 --> 00:59:10,000
Soon your Atlas will be covered in otherworldly domains.

1072
00:59:10,000 --> 00:59:19,000
In addition, like all items in PoE, you can craft them. Use your currency to add mods to your tablets, allowing you to upgrade all the Breaches in range.

1073
00:59:19,000 --> 00:59:30,000
Tablets can have up to two mods. These mods do things like adding extra rare monsters, extra clasped hands, or even mods to density of Breaches, allowing you to keep them open longer.

1074
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:40,000
Often, you will find multiple towers near to each other with overlapping areas of effect. This can allow you to really juice the mechanic by stacking the mods from multiple tablets.

1075
00:59:40,000 --> 00:59:46,000
In your fight to hold the Breach Demons at bay, you may want to use the powers of their world against them.

1076
00:59:46,000 --> 00:59:52,000
Each endgame mechanic always has player power that can only be gained from that mechanic, and Breach is no different.

1077
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:59,000
In Breach, you will find Catalysts, items that can increase the quality of rings and amulets by improving specific mods.

1078
00:59:59,000 --> 01:00:05,000
You can also find Breach Rings, a special base type that can have its quality improved by Catalysts up to 50%.

1079
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:09,000
In this case, you could create a ring with around 170 life.

1080
01:00:09,000 --> 01:00:15,000
Breach Rings can become some of the strongest rings in the game, giving you some good motivation to face the Demon Horns.

1081
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:19,000
In addition, each endgame mechanic needs to have a pinnacle endgame encounter.

1082
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:22,000
While killing Breach monsters, you may find Breach Splinters.

1083
01:00:22,000 --> 01:00:25,000
Collect enough of these and you'll be able to create a Breach Stone.

1084
01:00:25,000 --> 01:00:32,000
Using a vile technology called the Realm Gate, you can use your Breach Stone to access their domain and bring the fight to them.

1085
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:38,000
In this twisted domain, you will find nothing but a single massive Breach.

1086
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:41,000
Triggering it will reveal hordes of Breach inhabitants.

1087
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:56,000
And should you be fast enough, you will be able to fight their leader, Zest, We That Are One.

1088
01:00:56,000 --> 01:01:08,000
We that dreamed, We in nightmare, We that are one.

1089
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:12,000
Fate relies truth.

1090
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,000
Fawak'd sayendenki be a great hero of Bollywood, now we use Mine.

1091
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:31,000
ALL we're numbered biết in the future are under hierarchies in the game.

1092
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:35,000
of PoE too. We won't be showing the rest of them, so you will have to discover them for yourself.

1093
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:39,000
But rest assured, this is some of the hardest content we have ever made.

1094
01:01:39,000 --> 01:01:43,000
All these encounters have specific uniques that can only be found from them.

1095
01:01:43,000 --> 01:01:47,000
But that's not all. We still have the progression system.

1096
01:01:47,000 --> 01:01:52,000
Defeating Zest will give you points to allocate into the Breach section of the Atlas tree.

1097
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:56,000
Allocating these points will make Breaches and the Breach domain even harder,

1098
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:58,000
but will give you more rewards.

1099
01:01:58,000 --> 01:02:01,000
The small nodes will increase the difficulty of the Twisted Domain,

1100
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:04,000
while the large nodes have more specific bonuses.

1101
01:02:04,000 --> 01:02:08,000
For example, this node adds more Clasped Hands to your Breaches,

1102
01:02:08,000 --> 01:02:11,000
and adds a pack of Magic Monsters that can guard them.

1103
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:14,000
Get some more points and you can allocate Waking Nightmare,

1104
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:17,000
which will double the number of splinters you get from Clasped Hands,

1105
01:02:17,000 --> 01:02:20,000
and inflict you with a mysterious debunk.

1106
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:24,000
In order to earn more points, you will need to defeat Zest at a higher difficulty,

1107
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:30,000
and some rewards from Zest can only be found by increasing the difficulty of the Twisted Domain above certain thresholds.

1108
01:02:30,000 --> 01:02:34,000
Defeating Zest at difficulty 4 will be a challenge indeed,

1109
01:02:34,000 --> 01:02:36,000
but there are many more threats in Wraeclast.

1110
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:42,000
Ritual Altars are sacrificial sites built by the mysterious King in the Mists.

1111
01:02:42,000 --> 01:02:49,000
If you encounter this symbol on the Atlas, then you know that the area contains Ritual Altars.

1112
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:51,000
Ritual Altars demand tribute.

1113
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:55,000
Every monster you slaughter in the Circle will feed the altar.

1114
01:02:55,000 --> 01:02:58,000
After the sacrifice, touch it to begin the ritual.

1115
01:02:58,000 --> 01:03:03,000
The monsters you just killed will be resurrected by the King of the Mists' dark magic,

1116
01:03:03,000 --> 01:03:08,000
and you must fight to survive.

1117
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:12,000
The tribute you have offered to the altar can be spent to buy powerful items,

1118
01:03:12,000 --> 01:03:14,000
but they can be expensive.

1119
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:17,000
To gain more tribute, you will want to find more altars.

1120
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:22,000
Each successive ritual you do within an area will spawn the monsters revived by the previous ones,

1121
01:03:22,000 --> 01:03:25,000
in addition to the ones you sacrificed next to them.

1122
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:29,000
By the end of an area, you will be fighting a truly imposing number of foes,

1123
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:32,000
but will have a significant amount of tribute to spend.

1124
01:03:32,000 --> 01:03:35,000
One of the rewards you can buy with tribute are omens.

1125
01:03:35,000 --> 01:03:37,000
These are special items that allow for metacrafting.

1126
01:03:37,000 --> 01:03:40,000
Crafting items that affect other crafting items.

1127
01:03:40,000 --> 01:03:43,000
Have an item with good prefixes but bad suffixes?

1128
01:03:43,000 --> 01:03:47,000
This omen will help you to remove the mods you don't want, while keeping the ones you do.

1129
01:03:47,000 --> 01:03:51,000
There are a bunch more of these with different effects, but we will leave them for you to discover.

1130
01:03:51,000 --> 01:03:54,000
Now don't forget that Ritual will also drop tablets,

1131
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:57,000
which can be used to specialize into getting more rituals.

1132
01:03:57,000 --> 01:04:01,000
If you want to get to the pinnacle boss of Ritual, then you will probably want to use them.

1133
01:04:01,000 --> 01:04:05,000
They can also be crafted to grant mods, making your rituals more rewarding.

1134
01:04:05,000 --> 01:04:09,000
The pinnacle encounter of Ritual is the King in the Mists.

1135
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:14,000
Feared by the Asmiri people, he is said to have brought eternal darkness to the Wildwood.

1136
01:04:14,000 --> 01:04:19,000
We won't show the encounter, but just like Breach, there are a range of unique items you can get for defeating him,

1137
01:04:19,000 --> 01:04:22,000
and you will gain points in the Ritual section of the Atlas Tree.

1138
01:04:22,000 --> 01:04:26,000
Some maps have been touched by insanity.

1139
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:30,000
A mysterious entity has taken a special interest in you.

1140
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:34,000
Step through the looking glass and you will find your nightmares coming to life.

1141
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:39,000
When you touch a mirror, the mists of Delirium will spread out across the area, infecting your mind.

1142
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:44,000
You must stay within the mist to maintain the nightmare, which is as profitable as it is terrifying.

1143
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:47,000
Everything you kill will increase the rewards that drop.

1144
01:04:47,000 --> 01:04:51,000
However, the deeper into the mist you travel, the stronger the monsters are.

1145
01:04:51,000 --> 01:04:54,000
Be careful not to overstay your welcome.

1146
01:04:54,000 --> 01:05:01,000
Rare and unique enemies will become vessels for terrifying demons, who will manifest out of them to unleash powerful attacks on you.

1147
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:04,000
The mist also offers a strange crafting material.

1148
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,000
Distilled Emotions.

1149
01:05:06,000 --> 01:05:12,000
By combining these Emotions, you are able to instill your amulet with a notable from the passive skill tree.

1150
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:15,000
This is like gaining an extra passive point for free, attached to your gear.

1151
01:05:15,000 --> 01:05:20,000
They are also particularly great because you don't have to traverse the tree to get them,

1152
01:05:20,000 --> 01:05:25,000
allowing you to get off-class bonuses that would normally be much harder to get.

1153
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:28,000
Distilled Emotions can also be used to instill your endgame maps,

1154
01:05:28,000 --> 01:05:32,000
applying Delirious to them and adding additional difficulty and rewards,

1155
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:35,000
allowing you to further juice your endgame maps.

1156
01:05:35,000 --> 01:05:39,000
The tablets you can find from Delirium can be used to further improve it,

1157
01:05:39,000 --> 01:05:42,000
increase pack size, make the fog dissipate slower,

1158
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:45,000
or improve your progress towards the pinnacle encounter of Delirium.

1159
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:50,000
Speaking of which, every now and then you will find Simulacrum Splinters.

1160
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:55,000
The mysterious entity will create strange encounters based on warped versions of your own memories.

1161
01:05:55,000 --> 01:06:00,000
Monsters and Simulacrums come in waves that get progressively more difficult.

1162
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:02,000
You will receive loot at the end of each wave,

1163
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:05,000
and you will have to make the decision to leave now or continue on,

1164
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:08,000
facing up against even tougher foes from the mist.

1165
01:06:08,000 --> 01:06:14,000
The bosses you will face as you get deeper into a Simulacrum are truly terrifying.

1166
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:19,000
If you can complete a Simulacrum, you will gain points for the Delirium section of the Atlas skill tree.

1167
01:06:19,000 --> 01:06:23,000
Next up we have Expedition.

1168
01:06:23,000 --> 01:06:29,000
Occasionally, while clearing Corruption, you will encounter these Kalgurin settlers.

1169
01:06:29,000 --> 01:06:33,000
The Kalgurins have discovered ancient burial sites with lost Varicium artifacts,

1170
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:37,000
and they want you to help dig them up with explosives.

1171
01:06:37,000 --> 01:06:40,000
The Kalgurins have marked the locations where the relics can be found.

1172
01:06:40,000 --> 01:06:43,000
Place explosives as best you can to dig up as many as possible.

1173
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:45,000
There is just one problem.

1174
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:48,000
Corruption has brought the corpses of their ancestors to life,

1175
01:06:48,000 --> 01:06:52,000
so you might have to do a little clean up before you can reclaim the artifacts.

1176
01:06:52,000 --> 01:07:03,000
You can also find remnants, the destruction of which will further anger the restless dead.

1177
01:07:03,000 --> 01:07:08,000
Each one you blow up will make the subsequent monsters more powerful, but also more rewarding.

1178
01:07:08,000 --> 01:07:15,000
Danig, Rog, Tujan, and Gwennon will exchange the artifacts for useful items and runic magic.

1179
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:20,000
You can also find tablets to increase the number of expeditions and the rewards.

1180
01:07:20,000 --> 01:07:27,000
This one increases the radius of explosives, while this one increases the number of remnants you will find.

1181
01:07:27,000 --> 01:07:31,000
Eventually, you might discover a logbook.

1182
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:34,000
These are special maps full of buried treasure and relics.

1183
01:07:34,000 --> 01:07:38,000
Essentially one giant dig site.

1184
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:45,000
Here you can create an extremely long chain of explosives and go through a very high number of remnants.

1185
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:46,000
But be careful!

1186
01:07:46,000 --> 01:07:49,000
Many remnants have mods that can really break your build,

1187
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:51,000
so you will probably want to avoid these ones.

1188
01:07:51,000 --> 01:07:55,000
If you add too many remnants, you could easily make the encounter harder than you can handle.

1189
01:07:55,000 --> 01:07:59,000
There are all sorts of interesting things buried under the ground in logbooks.

1190
01:07:59,000 --> 01:08:02,000
You might find dripping caves and hidden pirate caches.

1191
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:08,000
But the most powerful encounter is Ulroth, the ancient undead commander of the Knights of the Sun.

1192
01:08:08,000 --> 01:08:10,000
Defeating him will grant you unique rewards,

1193
01:08:10,000 --> 01:08:14,000
as well as points to spend in the expedition section of the Atlas Tree.

1194
01:08:14,000 --> 01:08:18,000
So those are the endgame systems on the Atlas, but we are not done yet.

1195
01:08:18,000 --> 01:08:23,000
The trials we talked about earlier have much more content when you get to endgame too.

1196
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:28,000
Just like the other endgame systems, they also have progression mechanics, unique rewards,

1197
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:30,000
and player power that can only be gained from them.

1198
01:08:30,000 --> 01:08:36,000
As you get higher level coins for the trial of the Sekimers, you will unlock more floors to explore.

1199
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:48,000
Each floor has its own challenging brooms and a floor boss that you will need to kill.

1200
01:08:48,000 --> 01:08:53,000
There are four floors in total, leading to another pinnacle boss at the end of the last floor,

1201
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:55,000
which can only be accessed at endgame.

1202
01:08:55,000 --> 01:09:00,000
The trial of the Sekimers is where you'll find duels, which you can socket into your tree.

1203
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:03,000
These are like passives that you can craft with your currency items.

1204
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:09,000
They can be really powerful, as they allow you to stack modifiers that may not be easily accessible on the tree normally.

1205
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:13,000
This duel gives lightning damage and shock chance, for example.

1206
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:18,000
There are quite a few duel sockets on the tree, so it's possible to gain a lot of power here.

1207
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:24,000
There are also other types of duels that don't provide any bonuses themselves, but affect other passives surrounding them.

1208
01:09:24,000 --> 01:09:29,000
This duel increases the effect of small nodes and radius by 25%.

1209
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:33,000
With careful placement in the tree, you could get a significant amount of power from it.

1210
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:40,000
There are also unique duels available with very interesting effects, but you will have to find those for yourself.

1211
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:48,000
In order to push further into the trial and uncover the secrets of the Marakev, you will want to take advantage of its progression system, relics.

1212
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:52,000
Relics are items that can be placed in the Relic Altar as you start the trial.

1213
01:09:52,000 --> 01:09:57,000
They give special bonuses that affect the trial, making it easier and increasing its rewards.

1214
01:09:57,000 --> 01:10:02,000
Of course, you can craft these with your currency items, making them even stronger.

1215
01:10:02,000 --> 01:10:09,000
If you can complete the entire trial overcoming all four flaws, the final boss will reward you with one of many unique relics.

1216
01:10:09,000 --> 01:10:15,000
These relics will be consumed when used on your next run, but can reward you with unique and powerful items.

1217
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:18,000
For example, this is The Last Flame.

1218
01:10:18,000 --> 01:10:24,000
If you use it, you will have only one honour for the entire trial, so you will need to do a completely hitless run.

1219
01:10:24,000 --> 01:10:30,000
The Trial of Chaos also extends into the endgame.

1220
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:36,000
As you gain inscribed ultimatums of higher and higher levels, the number of chambers that you can go through increases.

1221
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:42,000
In true Vaal style, this allows you to take even more risks for even more rewards.

1222
01:10:42,000 --> 01:10:47,000
At endgame, you can progress through up to ten chambers with three bosses on a single run.

1223
01:10:47,000 --> 01:10:52,000
Stacking ten tribulations on top of each other will make this a significant challenge, but it's worth it.

1224
01:10:52,000 --> 01:10:57,000
The Trial Master will tempt you with items of the Vaal Empire, such as Vaal Orbs.

1225
01:10:57,000 --> 01:11:02,000
Vaal Orbs are powerful crafting items that corrupt your gear with random mysterious outcomes.

1226
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:10,000
Corruption prevents an item from being modified further, so it has to be the last step of your craft, but it's also the most impactful one.

1227
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:18,000
For example, if you use one on your body armour, it might add a new powerful enchantment, or it might reroll up to half of its modifiers.

1228
01:11:18,000 --> 01:11:25,000
Vaal Orbs also have the ability to add a socket, allowing you to bypass the normal restriction of how many sockets an item can have.

1229
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:31,000
A body armour could get up to three sockets this way, allowing for a significant number of mods.

1230
01:11:31,000 --> 01:11:34,000
Vaal Orbs can even modify uniques.

1231
01:11:34,000 --> 01:11:41,000
Adding enchantments or sockets to uniques can make them incredibly powerful, but there is a good chance that you will break them as well.

1232
01:11:41,000 --> 01:11:45,000
The Trial Master will also occasionally offer you Soul Cores.

1233
01:11:45,000 --> 01:11:53,000
Originally formed by Chaos, the Vaal sought to replicate Soul Cores through human sacrifice rituals and blood magic to power their civilisation.

1234
01:11:53,000 --> 01:11:59,000
Soul Cores are powerful socketable items, with mods that cannot be obtained from regular runes.

1235
01:11:59,000 --> 01:12:04,000
Like all endgame content, there is of course a pinnacle boss.

1236
01:12:04,000 --> 01:12:07,000
The final chamber will drop keys to this mysterious door.

1237
01:12:07,000 --> 01:12:10,000
Some say this is where the Trial Master himself resides.

1238
01:12:10,000 --> 01:12:13,000
Perhaps you are willing to take the risk to find out.

1239
01:12:14,000 --> 01:12:15,000
Had enough yet?

1240
01:12:15,000 --> 01:12:18,000
Because there is still just one more thing.

1241
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:21,000
The most difficult content in Path of Exile 2.

1242
01:12:21,000 --> 01:12:29,000
While mapping, you might come across this fortress that has emerged from underground, surrounded by an enormous maze riddled with danger.

1243
01:12:29,000 --> 01:12:34,000
Is the maze preventing something from getting in? Or something getting out?

1244
01:12:34,000 --> 01:12:41,000
This fortress is of ancient origin, and its construction has similarities to the towers and tablets that you have been using on your journey through the endgame.

1245
01:12:41,000 --> 01:12:45,000
It is clear from the entrance that there are three keys required to enter.

1246
01:12:45,000 --> 01:12:50,000
Local factions are vying for access to the fortress in order to seize the power they believe will be inside.

1247
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:55,000
Each of the faction's leaders have managed to get their hands on one of the keys, so you will need to defeat them.

1248
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:58,000
Each faction is led by an Uber Act boss.

1249
01:12:58,000 --> 01:13:05,000
You can see one of them inhabiting this city, but in order to fight him, you will first need to defeat their two lieutenants in the adjacent zones.

1250
01:13:05,000 --> 01:13:06,000
Be careful.

1251
01:13:06,000 --> 01:13:12,000
If you fail against either of the lieutenants, or to kill the leader, they will move on, and you will need to find them again.

1252
01:13:12,000 --> 01:13:15,000
Kill all the Uber bosses and you will gain access to the fortress.

1253
01:13:15,000 --> 01:13:20,000
We aren't going to spoil it, as we can't wait to see you guys attempt it for the first time.

1254
01:13:20,000 --> 01:13:22,000
But is there a tree you get points in after killing it?

1255
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:23,000
Of course there is.

1256
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:26,000
This is Path of Exile. There is always another tree.

1257
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:28,000
So these are your challenges for PoE 2.

1258
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:31,000
As you can see, this project is crazy huge.

1259
01:13:31,000 --> 01:13:34,000
Way bigger than even we expected when we started out.

1260
01:13:34,000 --> 01:13:36,000
But how do you gain access?

1261
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:38,000
Well, during early access you'll need a key to get in.

1262
01:13:38,000 --> 01:13:45,000
To thank our existing PoE supporters who have spent more than $480 US dollars, we'll be giving you guys a key for the PC version for free.

1263
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:52,000
Anyone else who wants one can get one by purchasing one of the new early access supporter packs that have just been released to the store.

1264
01:13:52,000 --> 01:13:58,000
If you just want early access to PoE 2, then you can get a key in the $30 US dollar early access pack.

1265
01:13:58,000 --> 01:14:02,000
The pack also comes with $30 of points to spend in the MTX store.

1266
01:14:02,000 --> 01:14:10,000
But we also have a variety of other supporter packs filled with exclusive microtransactions, points to spend in the store, and even physical items.

1267
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:15,000
The cosmetics can be used right now in PoE 1 and in Path of Exile 2 when early access starts.

1268
01:14:15,000 --> 01:14:21,000
Most of this footage has been recorded in Path of Exile 1, since that's where you can use them immediately.

1269
01:14:21,000 --> 01:14:26,000
The Lord of Ogham supporter pack contains a cosmetic armour set befitting of the Count of Ogham himself.

1270
01:14:26,000 --> 01:14:32,000
