It replaces the default appearance of any foci to an ancient relic once used by Dooyani, and this can be applied to shields in Path of Exile 1.

1304
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:33,000
That's not the only Vile weapon you'll find. It also contains the Wand of the Thaumaturge skin.

1305
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:36,000
And the Royal Sacrifice dagger skin.

1306
01:17:38,000 --> 01:17:41,000
You wouldn't think to put sacrificial gems on a Kiwi, but the Vile did.

1307
01:17:42,000 --> 01:17:46,000
Thaumaturge of the Vile supporters will receive the Thaumaturge of the Vile Kiwi pet.

1308
01:17:47,000 --> 01:17:51,000
And the Statue of Dominus. This is also the first pack in the series with a physical item.

1309
01:17:52,000 --> 01:17:55,000
When purchasing this pack, you'll receive a Path of Exile 2 logo t-shirt.

1310
01:17:56,000 --> 01:18:00,000
But if you don't want one, you can opt out and return for additional points to spend in the store.

1311
01:18:00,000 --> 01:18:09,000
Becoming a Warlord of the Kaorui supporter will grant you an armor set and back attachment, adorned in jade carvings and iridescent feathers resembling power.

1312
01:18:10,000 --> 01:18:15,000
Enough to even impress the Ancestral Gods, specifically Tukuhama, the Kaorui God of War.

1313
01:18:15,000 --> 01:18:21,000
Overkill, you say? I think the Kaorui people would disagree.

1314
01:18:22,000 --> 01:18:25,000
Why not drop a gigantic totem on rare enemies you slay to crush them to a pulp?

1315
01:18:26,000 --> 01:18:30,000
Replace your crafting bench in your hideout with the Ancestral Canoe crafting bench,

1316
01:18:30,000 --> 01:18:37,000
where Ancestral Chief Mata will summon a giant canoe manned by Kaorui warriors to aid in your crafting desires.

1317
01:18:38,000 --> 01:18:40,000
We must all start somewhere.

1318
01:18:42,000 --> 01:18:44,000
You'll also get a pair of weapon skins.

1319
01:18:45,000 --> 01:18:49,000
Equip Akoya's Felling Axe skin to your one-hand or two-handed axes,

1320
01:18:50,000 --> 01:18:52,000
or Tukuhama's Crusher to your one-handed or two-handed maces.

1321
01:18:53,000 --> 01:18:58,000
A true Kaorui warlord is always accompanied by their trusty Kiwi.

1322
01:18:59,000 --> 01:19:03,000
Equipped with armor and harnessing Ancestral Magic, they make the perfect sidekick.

1323
01:19:04,000 --> 01:19:10,000
Once one of the most feared beings in Wraeclast, Malachi was slain by a powerful exile.

1324
01:19:11,000 --> 01:19:14,000
May the statue commemorate the virtue of exile's past, present and of the future.

1325
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:18,000
Of course, it's not all about dressing up in game.

1326
01:19:19,000 --> 01:19:20,000
You'll want to look good in real life too.

1327
01:19:20,000 --> 01:19:24,000
By becoming a Warlord of the Kaorui supporter, you'll also get a Path of Exile 2 hoodie.

1328
01:19:25,000 --> 01:19:29,000
Our final tier of supporter pack in this series is the Liberator of Wraeclast supporter pack.

1329
01:19:30,000 --> 01:19:35,000
The Liberator of Wraeclast armor set and back attachment come made with the finest materials in Wraeclast,

1330
01:19:36,000 --> 01:19:38,000
and shattered glass mosaics suspended in divine power.

1331
01:19:39,000 --> 01:19:43,000
Set up your base of operations in the Beacon of Salvation hideout.

1332
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:46,000
Why restrict yourself to just one island when you can liberate more?

1333
01:19:46,000 --> 01:19:54,000
The Beacon of Salvation hideout comes equipped with your own collection of small islands and personal operators of boats that you can use to row between them.

1334
01:19:55,000 --> 01:19:58,000
Just walk to the piers, click a boat to enter and navigate as you choose.

1335
01:19:59,000 --> 01:20:02,000
Decorate each island as you see fit to best represent your well-earned hideout.

1336
01:20:02,000 --> 01:20:06,000
Everyone in your hideout can use their own boat. Why not have some racers?

1337
01:20:07,000 --> 01:20:10,000
You can also get the Window to Twilight portal effect.

1338
01:20:11,000 --> 01:20:16,000
A beautiful mosaic piece of art that shatters and reveals a gateway to your desired destination as you approach it.

1339
01:20:16,000 --> 01:20:20,000
As you walk away, the glass magically reforms back to its original form.

1340
01:20:22,000 --> 01:20:25,000
Rule in style with the Throne of the Ruler map device.

1341
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:31,000
Sure, this map device can create portals to endgame maps, but it also comes with a throne you can sit on to oversee your growing kingdom.

1342
01:20:32,000 --> 01:20:34,000
Look down on the plebeians running your maps.

1343
01:20:35,000 --> 01:20:38,000
Being the Liberator though is not just about sitting in your throne all day.

1344
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:43,000
If you do decide to join the fight yourself, you can leave a High Priest in charge as your second in command.

1345
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:49,000
Liberator of Rhaeclast supporters will also get a set of varied weapon skins.

1346
01:20:50,000 --> 01:20:52,000
The Light of Divinity Scepter skin.

1347
01:20:53,000 --> 01:20:54,000
The Deliverance Crossbow skin.

1348
01:20:55,000 --> 01:20:56,000
The Justice Flail skin.

1349
01:20:57,000 --> 01:20:58,000
And the Redemption Shield skin.

1350
01:20:59,000 --> 01:21:07,000
Once again, you'll have an Accompany in Kiwi, and of course a statue depicting one of the most iconic events in Rhaeclast's history.

1351
01:21:08,000 --> 01:21:11,000
The battle between a powerful exile and Kitava, the Insatiable.

1352
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:16,000
With the help of two deities, Sin and Innocence, the exile was able to defeat him once and for all.

1353
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:20,000
This supporter pack also contains the Path of Exile 2 art book.

1354
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:29,000
This 215 page full colour art book includes a huge amount of amazing concept art and lore, produced during the long and exciting journey of Path of Exile 2's development.

1355
01:21:30,000 --> 01:21:35,000
And finally, Path of Exile has a tradition of letting the community participate in designing game features.

1356
01:21:35,000 --> 01:21:39,000
For Path of Exile 2 we'll be adding the Twilight Order foil reliquary.

1357
01:21:40,000 --> 01:21:51,000
By becoming a Liberator of Rhaeclast supporter, once Path of Exile 2 is released, you will be able to select any unique item you have found, and be able to drop it from the reliquary.

1358
01:21:51,000 --> 01:22:00,000
Once players have submitted their items, keys to the reliquary will start dropping, and other players will be able to find foil versions of uniques that you have submitted along with a message for the lucky player.

1359
01:22:01,000 --> 01:22:06,000
The more players submit the same unique, the more chances there will be for the reliquary to drop them, so choose wisely.

1360
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:10,000
Now almost all of these items are available to use in PoE 1 right now.

1361
01:22:11,000 --> 01:22:15,000
There are a few exceptions where the item class clearly doesn't exist, such as crossbows or flails.

1362
01:22:16,000 --> 01:22:20,000
And there are also a few microtransactions on weapon types that are unavailable in PoE 2 at the start of Early Access.

1363
01:22:21,000 --> 01:22:25,000
Once classes that use those weapon types are added, those microtransactions will be available to use.

1364
01:22:25,000 --> 01:22:33,000
If you can't decide which supporter pack to choose yet, you can always start with the Early Access Supporter Pack, that just includes a key and some points to spend in the store.

1365
01:22:34,000 --> 01:22:37,000
Then you can upgrade to any of the following tiers at a later date.

1366
01:22:38,000 --> 01:22:41,000
These Supporter Packs will be available for purchase throughout Early Access.

